  "title": "AMRI 16-N-0031 sleep1",
  "description": "An overnight EEG-fMRI study conducted at the Advanced MRI section of NINDS/NIH, examining sleep physiology through simultaneous electroencephalography and functional magnetic resonance imaging. This pilot study involved multiple subjects who underwent two consecutive nights of approximately 8-hour scanning sessions with randomized arousal stimuli administered 8 times per night. This pilot investigation (sleep1) established protocols later expanded in a larger follow-up study (sleep2).",
  "methods_description": "Overnight EEG-fMRI acquisition performed over two consecutive nights for approximately 8 hours per session. Subjects were aroused at random intervals 8 times during each night. This pilot study established the protocols and procedures that were subsequently expanded in the sleep2 investigation.",
